<tool name="test_code_evaluator_draft">
  <description>Run the current code-evaluator draft in the mounted form preview path and return the preview result to PXI.</description>
  <when_to_use>
    - After reading the draft and the user asks for or agrees to a preview test.
    - When you need execution feedback before deciding whether to revise the evaluator or test payload again.
  </when_to_use>
  <preflight>
    - Call `read_code_evaluator_draft` first if you want to confirm the current draft before testing.
  </preflight>
  <guidelines>
    - When validating multiple examples, send all of them in one `cases` call with unique IDs instead of repeatedly editing `testPayload` and testing one case at a time.
    - A `cases` call uses temporary payload overrides. It does not change the form and does not require edit approval. Omit `cases` to preview the form's current `testPayload` as before.
    - Treat preview failures as iteration signals: inspect each case's error/result, revise the source if needed, and test the relevant cases again.
    - This tool does not create or update an evaluator. The user must still click Create or Update from the form when they are satisfied.
  </guidelines>
</tool>
